sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS schedule_count
FROM ad_schedules
WHERE scheduled_date = '2023-10-01';

external_knowledge:
- Engagement rate and click-through rate (CTR) are metrics used to measure the success of ads; 
- The year 2023 is the time frame for ad performance evaluation;
- Impressions, clicks, and reach are common metrics in advertising, where impressions refer to the number of times an ad is displayed, clicks are the number of times users click on the ad, and reach refers to the number of unique users who viewed the ad.

- A click-through rate (CTR) is a measure of the number of clicks an ad receives divided by the number of times it's shown (impressions).; 
- Cost per thousand impressions (CPM) refers to the cost of an ad campaign divided by the number of impressions, multiplied by 1000.; 
- Engagement rate is a measure of the interactions (likes, shares, comments, etc.) that a piece of content receives compared to the number of people who viewed it.; 
- Average feedback ratings are used to gauge the overall satisfaction or sentiment towards something, in this case, the campaigns.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT p.program_name
FROM ad_schedules ads
JOIN programs p ON ads.program_id = p.program_id;
